I've been living in fear all this time

114
00:09:57,630 --> 00:10:00,530
that you'd yell at me for my poor grades.

115
00:10:00,530 --> 00:10:04,720
I feel strangely futile right now.

116
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,100
Are you satisfied with these grades?

117
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,930
Say something like that?

118
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,260
You're so annoying.

119
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,450
 Nu Ri. 

120
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:17,080
How come you're here so early today?

121
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,940
I preferred coming to school early.

122
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:23,050
Let's go.

123
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:29,330
Hold on tight, Choi Sa Rang.

124
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:54,610
 

125
00:11:09,740 --> 00:11:11,150
You're up early.

126
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,660
I was about to come up.

127
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:15,930
It feels like I haven't seen you forever,
but it's only been a few days.

128
00:11:15,930 --> 00:11:18,090
Good to see you, Sunbae.

129
00:11:18,090 --> 00:11:19,680
What?

130
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,070
You didn't get to sleep again?

131
00:11:21,070 --> 00:11:24,210
I'm practicing sleeping without sleeping pills.

132
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,560
I just brushed my teeth.

133
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:29,920
Good. Let's wash your salon at the hair.

134
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,670
No, wash your salon...

135
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:37,080
It sounds like you're the one
who didn't get any sleep.

136
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,140
Right.

137
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,230
I didn't get good sleep. Yeah.

138
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:41,660
Let's go.

139
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,620
We'll go in self-driving mode.

140
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,290
Okay.

141
00:11:49,070 --> 00:11:50,250
Hello, everyone.

142
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:53,300
This is the set of "Famished for Love."

143
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:57,330
This air, this weather, this sun, this breeze...

144
00:11:57,330 --> 00:12:02,010
It's such a pity that I get
to enjoy this by myself.

145
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:05,950
This project is really living up to its name.

146
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:07,440
What?

147
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,200
"What's up? LOL"?

148
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:14,410
Why would he be curious about what you're up to?

149
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:15,580
Does he not have a job?

150
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:17,170
Tell him to volunteer or something.

151
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:19,170
Stop. He's just a kid.

152
00:12:19,170 --> 00:12:22,510
This is just the beginning
of his being interested in me.

153
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:27,620
"Thinking of you~"

154
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:30,140
Were you really thinking of him?

155
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,920
It's a lie.

156
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:38,800
Hey, Tae Rin, you know...

157
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:44,060
Do you think not disliking someone
means liking that person?

158
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:47,820
Not disliking doesn't equal liking, right?

159
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:49,900
So, there's some interest.

160
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:52,430
This is so unlike you. Why do you ask?

161
00:12:52,430 --> 00:12:54,440
Is this about someone you know?

162
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:58,840
Oh, yes, she's wondering if it's
enough for her to date someone.

163
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:02,370
What would be enough to date someone?

164
00:13:02,370 --> 00:13:03,930
Not sure.

165
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:07,940
Maybe if your heart is 100% sold?

166
00:13:07,940 --> 00:13:12,700
How would you know if you're 100% sold?

167
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:19,600
I don't know who this is,
but they sound so square.

168
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:25,330
Sounds like they'll be alone for the
rest of their lives without ever dating.

169
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:30,440
If he has a decent personality and
you have shared hobbies, it's a go.

170
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:34,530
Of course, a nice voice gets bonus points for me.

171
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:39,900
But isn't it nice when someone
who rejected me is begging?

172
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,700
Is that good?

173
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:49,280
Well, I'm not talking about myself.

174
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:53,200
I need some air.

175
00:13:57,740 --> 00:14:01,230
She's so cute. Seriously.

176
00:14:01,230 --> 00:14:06,360
 

177
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:14,170
You're here.

178
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:15,870
When can I see you on TV?

179
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:17,910
I'm getting chills.

180
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:19,980
How did you know we're almost done filming?

181
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:23,130
Because you're here for the first time in a while.

182
00:14:24,810 --> 00:14:27,390
Did you get your blood drawn?

183
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:30,230
- What did they say at the hospital?
- The same.

184
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:33,730
