about how I'm going to cling.

225
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:36,830
So, what led you to kiss her out of the blue?

226
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:39,710
I wasn't really thinking at the time.

227
00:16:39,710 --> 00:16:42,030
Are you an idiot or trash?

228
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:46,800
This is the last day of the shoot.

229
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,990
I'm thinking we'll have you write letters.

230
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:50,880
To Beat and Bebop.

231
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,720
As a final gesture.

232
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:56,220
We'll send you the letter you write
today a year from now.

233
00:16:56,220 --> 00:16:59,840
Do you have any ideas about the letter?

234
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,400
- Me!
- Geez.

235
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:04,280
I subscribe to a will-writing service.

236
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:05,700
It changes content every year.

237
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:08,770
It's nice because it feels like
doing end-of-year accounting.

238
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:10,960
A will...

239
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:14,220
Why are you doing stuff like that?

240
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:16,840
A letter to my younger self...

241
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:18,820
It's something like that.

242
00:17:18,820 --> 00:17:21,940
Makes me reflect on what remains with me.

243
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:23,620
It's similar to a will.

244
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:26,140
Beat, you're so trendy.

245
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:35,960
- Wait.
- What?

246
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,740
- Let me.
- No!

247
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:40,740
Seriously, you're so petty.

248
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:46,260
Gosh, to me, you two seem exactly
the same as you did back then.

249
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:48,530
You're the same age as me.

250
00:17:48,530 --> 00:17:51,470
You're not that much older.

251
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:53,930
Bebop is laughing more and more.

252
00:17:53,930 --> 00:17:56,220
And Beat looks more comfortable.

253
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:57,510
No!

254
00:17:57,510 --> 00:18:01,270
Should we make this a regular program?
Not just a pilot?

255
00:18:01,270 --> 00:18:02,690
 No! 

256
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:04,760
- Just once.
- No!

257
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:11,060
I have no problem writing this.

258
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,360
But look at this Oppa.

259
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:15,260
You haven't written a single word.

260
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,560
- Don't.
- So lame.

261
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:21,270
Aigoo!

262
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:23,170
Can I curse a little?

263
00:18:23,170 --> 00:18:24,800
You can't curse at all.

264
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,140
Okay...

265
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:30,380
The most important project is the
three-part series, "A World Made of Ash."

266
00:18:30,380 --> 00:18:31,990
It's a tentpole.

267
00:18:31,990 --> 00:18:34,970
Sounds familiar. When did I see it recently?

268
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:37,800
You all read it, right? What do you think?

269
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:45,800
An adaptation that took a whole
year turned out like this?

270
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,990
The co-producer has the copyright,
so I trusted them.

271
00:18:47,990 --> 00:18:50,050
And look how it turned out.

272
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:52,600
We shouldn't have taken it just
because it's a huge production.

273
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,940
Vice President, is it just me?

274
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:01,580
Today is going to be a tough one.

275
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:17,800
 The sub MC for our show will be
a different actor, unfortunately. 

276
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:21,700
 My daughter will reach out.
Thanks in advance for the critique! 

277
00:19:23,210 --> 00:19:25,190
What a shame.

278
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:30,120
 Yes, thank you! 

279
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,300
 

280
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:37,350
What is Director Bang Han Na up to these days?

281
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:39,770
Tell me if you hear anything.

282
00:19:39,770 --> 00:19:42,580
We're close enough to send flowers, aren't we?

283
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:44,000
Okay.

284
00:19:45,780 --> 00:19:49,000
It feels weird without Director Han Na here.

285
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:52,700
- Is it just me?
- Yes, you're the only one.

286
00:20:33,070 --> 00:20:35,120
It's nice and sunny here.

287
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:38,700
Should we go with this place?
There's also a park nearby.

288
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:43,170
A four-story building without an elevator...

289
00:20:43,170 --> 00:20:45,250
You're trying to work out?

290
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:47,630
That is my goal, but...

291
00:20:48,950 --> 00:20:50,770
Are you worried now that you're actually here?

292
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:55,580
No. I've been worried even before I came.

293
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:33,730
Hyung, I just noticed grass I haven't seen before.
Looks like weeds.

294
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:35,760
Can I just pull them out?

295
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:41,800
Won't they fire you if you work like this?

296
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,950
I might get fired soon.

297
00:21:43,950 --> 00:21:46,760
With the bad economy, I have much less work.

298
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:48,820
I might need to run sales.

299
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:50,860
Aigoo...

300
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:53,000
Looking at you like that,

301
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,920
I feel like you're Cinderella
and I'm the evil sister.

302
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:57,860
To be exact, more like the Grasshopper.

303
00:21:57,860 --> 00:22:00,490
And this grass you were about to pull out.

304
00:22:00,490 --> 00:22:03,850
It was always here with you.

305
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:07,430
"The Ant and the Grasshopper."

306
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:09,040
Gosh, I hate bugs.

307
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,940
Let's just go with Cinderella.

308
00:22:10,940 --> 00:22:13,070
Sure.

309
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:17,600
Hyung, that still hasn't died.

310
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:21,830
I bought it at your opening,
so it's been three years.

311
00:22:21,830 --> 00:22:24,060
Must be.

312
00:22:24,060 --> 00:22:25,810
It was withering at first.

313
00:22:25,810 --> 00:22:28,180
Looks like I don't need to worry anymore.

314
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:31,630
I must be talented.

315
00:22:32,630 --> 00:22:35,510
I came every time you called me to say it's dying.

316
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:37,710
You have zero talent.

317
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:39,670
Move.

318
00:22:40,670 --> 00:22:43,210
You said to let you know
if there's an issue with that.

319
00:22:43,210 --> 00:22:45,070
You said it wasn't doing so well
when you sold it to me.

320
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:48,100
Change the order. It started having
issues after you bought it.

321
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:51,140
Hardship is necessary for a beautiful bloom.

322
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:55,700
Gosh, I'm glad it's growing nicely.
Both this flower and you.

323
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,760
Gosh, seriously...

324
00:22:58,730 --> 00:23:00,970
This one's dead.

325
00:23:00,970 --> 00:23:03,450
I need to cut it off completely.
Give me the scissors.

326
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:04,850
Sure.

327
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,380
Seriously...

328
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,600
Yes, it's Kim Seok Joo.

329
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,970
Gosh, I feel so bad.

330
00:23:21,620 --> 00:23:24,760
Who are you? A new gardener?

331
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,520
Hello.

332
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:43,590
Where did the original guy go?

333
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:45,600
He used to do a great job.

334
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:49,370
Hyung, no more grass pulling. Drive, please.

335
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:55,830
- Mom.
- Why is he your hyung?

336
00:23:57,830 --> 00:23:59,000
Your husband's son.

337
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,680
Why is my husband's son pulling grass here?

338
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:02,980
Your son made me.

339
00:24:02,980 --> 00:24:05,900
So, you do everything you're asked to do?

340
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:09,690
- Why did you ask him to do this?
- Because he's better than me.

341
00:24:09,690 --> 00:24:11,320
Why are you home at this hour?

342
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,850
I had a bad day, so I came home
for a change of scenery.

343
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:16,650
But now, I feel worse.

344
00:24:16,650 --> 00:24:19,670
I wanted to go on a drive with my Chan.

345
00:24:21,530 --> 00:24:23,540
That was gross what she said.

346
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:25,950
Love of the century, I guess.

347
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:33,240
Give me money.

348
00:24:39,410 --> 00:24:41,370
Just a moment.

349
00:24:41,370 --> 00:24:43,800
Why are you asking me for money?

350
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:48,360
"Sunwoo Hae shall serve Kim Seok Joo
for taking care of

351
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:52,090
his sister Eun Nu Ri during his military service

352
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:55,020
until he is satisfied."

353
00:24:55,020 --> 00:24:56,100
When will you be satisfied?

354
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:58,900
"If Hae violates this, they shall live together."

355
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:01,320
Let's live together. Sure.

356
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:05,130
Because of you, I delayed my studies
to take care of her.

357
00:25:05,130 --> 00:25:09,630
Hey. You ran back to Korea
when I asked you to take care of her.

358
00:25:09,630 --> 00:25:12,950
You cried your eyes out when I took Nu Ri back.

359
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:15,290
Aren't you grateful? You work at my shop.

360
00:25:15,290 --> 00:25:18,100
The shop belongs to me. You just funded it.

361
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:21,150
You're so weird. I'll need to bill you extra.

362
00:25:21,150 --> 00:25:23,970
I didn't know my mom was coming, either.

363
00:25:23,970 --> 00:25:26,760
Really. I swear.

364
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,840
It's just that...

365
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:37,000
while your mom and that moron had all the fun...

366
00:25:40,710 --> 00:25:44,260
Never mind. It's all my fault.

367
00:25:44,260 --> 00:25:47,340
Right, it's your fault.
Why are you taking my money?

368
00:25:47,340 --> 00:25:48,870
Give me a ride to my office.

369
00:25:48,870 --> 00:25:51,470
I didn't bring my car. Take the bus.

370
00:25:51,470 --> 00:25:53,130
Why aren't you driving the car I gave you?

371
00:25:53,130 --> 00:25:54,880
Let go of me!

372
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:01,350
Hello?

373
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:05,000
Yes. I'm Sunwoo Hae.

374
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,830
 We noticed something abnormal
in your blood sample. 

375
00:26:07,830 --> 00:26:11,550
 You'll need to do additional tests. 

376
00:26:14,220 --> 00:26:16,160
Why?

377
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:18,300
But I'm healthy.

378
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:20,640
I've been fine all along.

379
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,100
How long will the tests take?

380
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:32,290
I need to open up my business, even if it's late.

381
00:26:32,290 --> 00:26:33,860
My business, yes.

382
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:37,400
 

383
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:59,230
One, two, three...

384
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:28,300
 I brought you a bribe. 

385
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:31,530
 Wear these if you get hurt. 

386
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:41,170
I miss her.

387
00:27:46,690 --> 00:27:48,150
 

388
00:27:49,690 --> 00:27:51,530
Bye.

389
00:27:53,110 --> 00:27:55,100
 

390
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:58,830
You don't need the company car
today, right? Key, please.

391
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:00,340
Sure...

392
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:02,530
You're going to see So Min's film?

393
00:28:02,530 --> 00:28:04,060
Eat first. It's a long movie.

394
00:28:04,060 --> 00:28:06,570
Yes, I need to monitor...

395
00:28:06,570 --> 00:28:09,070
Isn't your phone vibrating? Not picking up?

396
00:28:09,070 --> 00:28:11,070
It's what I've been waiting for...

397
00:28:11,070 --> 00:28:13,030
You should take it, then. Bye.

398
00:28:13,030 --> 00:28:15,620
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

399
00:28:20,210 --> 00:28:21,350
 

400
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:27,840
Hello?

401
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:29,720
 Yeah. What are you up to? 

402
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:32,470
Doing something. Why?

403
00:28:32,470 --> 00:28:34,240
I miss you.

404
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,730
Okay. What?

405
00:28:36,730 --> 00:28:38,430
 I need to give you the appearance agreement. 

406
00:28:38,430 --> 00:28:41,360
 I signed it. Don't you need it? 

407
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,880
Well...

408
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,740
I'll get it.

409
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:50,210
I'll send a courier service.

410
00:28:50,210 --> 00:28:52,630
 Text me where to meet up. 

411
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:57,270
H-Hel...

412
00:28:57,270 --> 00:28:59,800
Hello? H-Hello?

413
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:04,840
What the heck?

414
00:29:07,190 --> 00:29:11,610
"I miss you"?

415
00:29:33,930 --> 00:29:35,460
Sung Je Yeon.

416
00:29:38,370 --> 00:29:41,670
Just be calm... Just be calm...

417
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:44,470
- Did you take a cab?
- Just be calm...

418
00:29:44,470 --> 00:29:46,420
- What?
- What?

419
00:29:46,420 --> 00:29:48,230
- What?
- Yeah.

420
00:29:48,230 --> 00:29:51,340
Oh, yes. W-What about you?

421
00:29:51,340 --> 00:29:54,200
Cab? Car?

422
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:59,120
I only drive when I need to.
When I have a lot of stuff.

423
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:01,700
You should be driving a truck then.

424
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:04,010
Why drive a foreign car?

425
00:30:05,850 --> 00:30:07,340
I know, huh?

426
00:30:08,130 --> 00:30:11,010
Why did I buy a car when I didn't
even have a driver's license?

427
00:30:11,010 --> 00:30:13,030
Are you talking to yourself?

428
00:30:13,030 --> 00:30:15,730
Oh, it's not my car.

429
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:20,350
What crazy person would entrust
someone with their car?

430
00:30:20,350 --> 00:30:22,630
Kim Seok Joo.

431
00:30:22,630 --> 00:30:24,530
Everything makes sense.

432
00:30:27,170 --> 00:30:30,400
What about the appearance agreement?

433
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:34,390
- Give it to you and get lost?
- No...

434
00:30:34,390 --> 00:30:36,060
I have a movie to watch.

435
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:38,800
If I miss it, I have to catch the early
morning screening tomorrow.

436
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:41,110
I guess we have no choice, then.

437
00:30:41,110 --> 00:30:43,090
I'll give it to you after the movie.

438
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:44,400
What?

439
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:47,190
What?

440
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:49,390
It's here.

441
00:30:49,390 --> 00:30:51,950
How did you know without paper tickets?

442
00:30:53,230 --> 00:30:54,970
What?

443
00:30:54,970 --> 00:30:58,130
When was the last time you watched a movie?

444
00:30:59,050 --> 00:31:00,830
I don't remember.

445
00:31:04,410 --> 00:31:06,500
It's been so long...

446
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:10,490
 Please check the emergency exits. 

447
00:31:10,490 --> 00:31:13,660
 The theater you're in right now is... 

448
00:31:13,660 --> 00:31:15,000
Enjoy.

449
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,960
Okay. You, too.

450
00:31:20,970 --> 00:31:22,530
It's starting.

451
00:31:36,870 --> 00:31:38,450
Here.

452
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:54,990
A hoobae submitted a letter
of resignation and said this.

453
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:57,940
That my path is not her path.

454
00:31:57,940 --> 00:32:00,450
She's leaving because she's scared of me.

455
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:05,000
So, I came home to see you,
but your son was there.

456
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,860
- Interesting, right?
- Very interesting.

457
00:32:07,860 --> 00:32:10,520
What? Hae came home?

458
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:13,100
That can't be. How did he get in?

459
00:32:13,100 --> 00:32:17,160
Seok Joo must've opened the door
for him. To make him his lackey.

460
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:20,110
They're still in touch...

461
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:22,350
What's the nature of their relationship?

462
00:32:22,350 --> 00:32:24,110
Are they dating?

463
00:32:25,060 --> 00:32:27,550
Want to ruin our family tree?

464
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:29,870
Not even over my dead body.

465
00:32:33,550 --> 00:32:37,230
I won't ask you to love Hae.

466
00:32:37,230 --> 00:32:40,030
Just don't hate him too much.

467
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:46,700
Who knows? I might've loved
him if he were like you.

468
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:53,550
I don't know what I'm feeling.

469
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:58,510
What's this side dish? It's delicious.

470
00:32:58,510 --> 00:33:01,940
You like greens with your liquor.

471
00:33:01,940 --> 00:33:04,410
I'm glad I made it earlier.

472
00:33:10,420 --> 00:33:12,450
Cheers.

473
00:33:17,300 --> 00:33:18,800
Cheers.

474
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,210
Cheers.

475
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:25,000
It's burning.

476
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,550
Here.

477
00:33:28,540 --> 00:33:31,830
What did you think about the movie?

478
00:33:31,830 --> 00:33:34,900
I'm curious since one of our actors is in it.

479
00:33:36,750 --> 00:33:38,210
Delicious.

480
00:33:39,210 --> 00:33:41,260
Want me to be honest?

481
00:33:41,260 --> 00:33:42,820
No.

482
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:47,370
I'm lost as to what to say in my feedback.

483
00:33:47,370 --> 00:33:50,690
Did you read the novel draft? What did you think?

484
00:33:50,690 --> 00:33:52,130
Want me to be honest?

485
00:33:52,130 --> 00:33:55,100
No. Prepare some cushioned language.

486
00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:58,490
She's at a sensitive age. She might get hurt.

487
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:09,570
You looked very focused
during the child actor scenes.

488
00:34:10,740 --> 00:34:13,180
Does it remind you of the old days?

489
00:34:13,180 --> 00:34:15,610
It's R-rated.

490
00:34:15,610 --> 00:34:20,500
I was thinking they can't even
watch the film they're in.

491
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:27,780
I was so annoyed about that.

492
00:34:27,780 --> 00:34:32,800
They used to make me hold ice in my mouth
when they could see my breath.

493
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:38,250
I had to cry and sob and drown myself.
Do all kinds of things.

494
00:34:38,250 --> 00:34:40,630
But I still wasn't allowed to watch it.

495
00:34:41,420 --> 00:34:44,460
I was thinking this when
we were filming with Tae Rin.

496
00:34:44,460 --> 00:34:47,600
It seems like you remember your entire childhood.

497
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:53,210
But you can't seem to remember only what I did.

498
00:34:54,250 --> 00:34:57,980
You can't remember what you did to me.

499
00:34:59,510 --> 00:35:03,200
Sung Je Yeon, this is in place
of your speech lessons.

500
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:05,690
All the child actors come here.

501
00:35:05,690 --> 00:35:08,130
 It's Sunwoo Hae! 

502
00:35:08,130 --> 00:35:10,070
Isn't that Bebop?

503
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:12,980
You're here.

504
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:14,920
Ma'am, you're here.

505
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,630
- Hello.
- How's your husband?

506
00:35:16,630 --> 00:35:18,470
Good, of course.

507
00:35:18,470 --> 00:35:20,110
Hae, say hi to your friend.

508
00:35:20,110 --> 00:35:21,510
Hi.

509
00:35:21,510 --> 00:35:24,030
- Ma'am, see me for a moment.
- Okay.

510
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:26,300
Your name is Hae?

511
00:35:26,300 --> 00:35:29,140
Wow, I saw you on TV.

512
00:35:32,210 --> 00:35:33,710
 Hey! 

513
00:35:34,950 --> 00:35:36,320
Why did you throw that out?

514
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,220
I bought that with my allowance!

515
00:35:38,220 --> 00:35:39,610
I don't need it anymore.

516
00:35:39,610 --> 00:35:41,670
We're not even friends.

517
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:45,380
 The acting studio you went to as a kid. 

518
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,770
 I went there, too. 

519
00:35:47,770 --> 00:35:49,750
 Forced by my mom. 

520
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:52,340
You were there?

521
00:35:52,340 --> 00:35:54,120
- Yeah.
- Don't mess with me.

522
00:35:54,120 --> 00:35:56,270
Wow...

523
00:35:56,270 --> 00:35:59,140
You really don't remember?

524
00:35:59,140 --> 00:36:03,850
Well, you were quite popular back then.

525
00:36:03,850 --> 00:36:07,180
- Are you serious?
- Why would I lie?

526
00:36:07,180 --> 00:36:08,870
I'm so sorry.

527
00:36:08,870 --> 00:36:12,570
I don't remember much about those times.

528
00:36:12,570 --> 00:36:15,310
I was constantly at the hospital.

529
00:36:15,310 --> 00:36:18,450
You have too many stories.

530
00:36:18,450 --> 00:36:21,370
Makes me scared of talking to you.

531
00:36:22,370 --> 00:36:24,510
Why were you at the hospital?

532
00:36:24,510 --> 00:36:26,770
Psychiatry?

533
00:36:26,770 --> 00:36:28,870
That, too.

534
00:36:28,870 --> 00:36:32,700
I wasn't feeling well, so I was
seeing different doctors.

535
00:36:32,700 --> 00:36:34,920
Aigoo.

536
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:37,370
Must've been tough for a kid.

537
00:36:37,370 --> 00:36:39,400
Are you okay now?

