00:57:35,790 --> 00:57:37,920
Did you get Tae Rin home okay?

810
00:57:37,920 --> 00:57:39,270
How was she?

811
00:57:39,270 --> 00:57:41,870
Why do you entrust your actress to someone else?

812
00:57:41,870 --> 00:57:43,820
- Weren't you nervous?
- I was.

813
00:57:43,820 --> 00:57:45,980
Tae Rin doesn't hold back, and you have no filter.

814
00:57:45,980 --> 00:57:49,000
And yet you entrusted someone
so dangerous to me?

815
00:57:50,320 --> 00:57:53,720
Hey, do you live here now?

816
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:55,130
Something like that.

817
00:57:55,950 --> 00:57:57,230
Hey.

818
00:57:58,250 --> 00:57:59,730
Teach me how to drive.

819
00:57:59,730 --> 00:58:03,160
Why would I teach you? Get an expert to teach you.

820
00:58:03,160 --> 00:58:05,760
Not just any lessons. Road driving practice.

821
00:58:05,760 --> 00:58:07,050
What are you talking about?

822
00:58:07,050 --> 00:58:09,980
I don't want to go to the driving school
because of an annoying guy.

823
00:58:11,520 --> 00:58:13,090
You really don't have a license?

824
00:58:13,090 --> 00:58:16,410
Did you say you only made one million won
from the stock info I shared last year?

825
00:58:16,410 --> 00:58:18,220
Can't believe you don't have
a license at your age.

826
00:58:18,220 --> 00:58:19,300
Want me to help you make 10 million?

827
00:58:19,300 --> 00:58:21,780
I guess it happens. When? Not today.

828
00:58:21,780 --> 00:58:24,280
I can't, either. I'm here to review
a contract for my mom.

829
00:58:24,280 --> 00:58:26,360
- How's tomorrow?
- I have to go on-site tomorrow.

830
00:58:26,360 --> 00:58:28,090
How's the day after?

831
00:58:28,090 --> 00:58:29,980
I have a blind date that day.

832
00:58:29,980 --> 00:58:32,290
How about the day after that? No, I can't make it.

833
00:58:32,290 --> 00:58:34,160
You don't need to practice driving?

834
00:58:34,160 --> 00:58:36,190
It is okay not to have a license on a blind date?

835
00:58:36,190 --> 00:58:38,610
It's okay since I have a great background.

836
00:58:38,610 --> 00:58:39,890
Let's find a time after my date.

837
00:58:39,890 --> 00:58:41,810
Why are you going on a blind date?

838
00:58:41,810 --> 00:58:43,650
Is the CEO making you?

839
00:58:43,650 --> 00:58:46,210
All because of the CEO of the company I work for.

840
00:58:46,210 --> 00:58:47,390
Plus, it's business.

841
00:58:47,390 --> 00:58:49,890
Wow, you're so busy.

842
00:58:55,830 --> 00:58:57,120
 This is Yu Eun Ji. 

843
00:58:57,120 --> 00:58:59,450
 I got your number from my dad. 

844
00:58:59,450 --> 00:59:02,440
 Can I get the feedback
on my writing after my exam? 

845
00:59:02,440 --> 00:59:04,490
I'm going crazy...

846
00:59:08,420 --> 00:59:11,470
 About the feedback for the
student you met last time... 

847
00:59:11,470 --> 00:59:13,120
Hae!

848
00:59:14,160 --> 00:59:15,940
Hand it over. I'll carry.

849
00:59:15,940 --> 00:59:17,580
Thank you.

850
00:59:17,580 --> 00:59:20,770
Gosh, looks like you had this
flower left over today.

851
00:59:20,770 --> 00:59:21,880
Yeah.

852
00:59:22,900 --> 00:59:25,500
Hyung, what should a reply look like?

853
00:59:25,500 --> 00:59:29,010
Just make sure you keep the phone on you.

854
00:59:29,010 --> 00:59:30,940
What do you know?

855
00:59:30,940 --> 00:59:32,220
Well, do you?

856
00:59:32,220 --> 00:59:35,410
The feeling of receiving flowers on just any day?

857
00:59:35,410 --> 00:59:39,940
It makes just any day suddenly special.

858
00:59:40,980 --> 00:59:43,320
Love that line.

859
00:59:43,320 --> 00:59:44,720
You should become a writer, Hyung.

860
00:59:44,720 --> 00:59:47,540
That's too big a compliment.

861
00:59:47,540 --> 00:59:49,090
I'll use it on a customer next time.

862
00:59:49,090 --> 00:59:52,050
"It makes just any day..." What was it?

863
00:59:52,050 --> 00:59:53,240
Suddenly special.

864
00:59:53,240 --> 00:59:56,700
"Suddenly special." That's pretty good.

865
00:59:56,700 --> 00:59:58,650
I feel insulted.

866
01:00:02,350 --> 01:00:03,620
Who sent this?

867
01:00:03,620 --> 01:00:05,420
The director of "A World Made of Ash."

868
01:00:05,420 --> 01:00:07,870
He sent premium pears.

869
01:00:07,870 --> 01:00:10,610
He always takes such great care of us.

870
01:00:10,610 --> 01:00:12,480
I'm overcome with gratitude.

871
01:00:12,480 --> 01:00:14,170
He got so rich off your novel.

872
01:00:14,170 --> 01:00:17,310
It doesn't feel right whenever he tries
to get by with sending something like this.

873
01:00:17,310 --> 01:00:20,630
You stopped writing after the movie worked out.

874
01:00:20,630 --> 01:00:22,050
Who did?

875
01:00:23,050 --> 01:00:25,070
- I stopped writing?
- You didn't?

876
01:00:25,070 --> 01:00:28,510
I'll think it was a win for the production
company when the film adaptation went well.

877
01:00:28,510 --> 01:00:31,690
Did you really write only to pay your bills?

878
01:00:31,690 --> 01:00:33,310
You never dreamed of the
Nobel Prize in literature?

879
01:00:33,310 --> 01:00:35,360
Who knew writing novels would bring in no money?

880
01:00:35,360 --> 01:00:37,990
Flowers don't make money, either.

881
01:00:37,990 --> 01:00:40,900
But I don't think that's so important in life.

882
01:00:40,900 --> 01:00:46,190
So, I hope you do everything you want
without worrying about money.

883
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:50,300
- You are so...
- I'm just me.

884
01:00:50,300 --> 01:00:52,460
Lee Geon No.

885
01:00:52,460 --> 01:00:54,940
Lee Geon No.

886
01:00:56,240 --> 01:00:58,960
You live like that, Hyung.

887
01:00:58,960 --> 01:01:02,150
I'll be thinking a lot about money.

888
01:01:04,650 --> 01:01:07,470
I wish this were money.

889
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,840
Wow, it's Actress Mo.

890
01:01:14,840 --> 01:01:16,440
Is this a still from the new show?

891
01:01:16,440 --> 01:01:22,260
Yes, they wanted selects for the
press release and promotion.

892
01:01:22,260 --> 01:01:25,630
Gosh, Tae Rin looks prettier on her other side.

893
01:01:25,630 --> 01:01:29,520
She closed her eyes here, but she
looks cute. Don't you think?

894
01:01:29,520 --> 01:01:34,550
You know that Tae Rin's contract
with our company ends this month, right?

895
01:01:34,550 --> 01:01:37,300
Have you talked to her?

896
01:01:37,300 --> 01:01:41,400
There's not much I can do.

897
01:01:41,400 --> 01:01:46,100
I just support Tae Rin's decisions.

898
01:01:48,300 --> 01:01:50,200
 

899
01:01:51,680 --> 01:01:53,400
You did last time, too.

900
01:01:53,400 --> 01:01:55,420
Did you have a fight with your phone?

901
01:01:56,320 --> 01:01:58,890
I wonder what he sent...

902
01:01:58,890 --> 01:02:01,070
You'd better check if you're curious.

903
01:02:01,070 --> 01:02:04,140
This one's pretty. Go with that one.

904
01:02:04,140 --> 01:02:07,630
You and your meaningless comments...

905
01:02:18,670 --> 01:02:20,670
 Okay. 

906
01:02:20,670 --> 01:02:22,290
Okay?

907
01:02:22,290 --> 01:02:25,130
 

908
01:02:31,210 --> 01:02:32,610
 

909
01:02:32,610 --> 01:02:35,050
"Sleet and Fog."

910
01:02:35,050 --> 01:02:36,670
"Waegeum."

911
01:02:37,720 --> 01:02:39,800
"A World Made of Ash."

912
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:43,290
You didn't check? We're already in pre-production.

913
01:02:43,290 --> 01:02:45,300
The actors from the first two series
stayed true to their words,

914
01:02:45,300 --> 01:02:47,220
and the main character signed
the appearance agreement!

915
01:02:47,220 --> 01:02:49,950
What will you do about this?

916
01:02:49,950 --> 01:02:53,650
What the hell have you been doing
with expired copyrights?

917
01:02:59,220 --> 01:03:02,700
Did you check with those who worked
on the first phase of the film adaptation?

918
01:03:02,700 --> 01:03:05,700
The copyright expiration of "A World Made of Ash."

919
01:03:05,700 --> 01:03:07,960
- Why did you just get here?
- I had a meeting.

920
01:03:07,960 --> 01:03:10,100
Many people had left the company.

921
01:03:10,100 --> 01:03:13,300
It's tough to hold the current staff accountable...

922
01:03:13,300 --> 01:03:17,900
Before you try to pin it on someone,
review other issues.

923
01:03:17,900 --> 01:03:19,470
Director, you have a solution, right?

924
01:03:19,470 --> 01:03:21,500
If we can't resolve this,
the third sequel will cancel.

925
01:03:21,500 --> 01:03:25,550
Why don't we start filming
and solve it eventually?

926
01:03:25,550 --> 01:03:27,680
 
The original author has kept quiet this whole time.

927
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:29,860
That's why it sounded familiar.

928
01:03:29,860 --> 01:03:32,910
It comes down to paying them
out if there's an issue.

929
01:03:32,910 --> 01:03:37,030
- We'll pay.
- Is that how you'd recoup the investment?

930
01:03:37,030 --> 01:03:40,520
Just be pathetic and say you'd step down!

931
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:42,750
Kim Pil Du, are you crazy?

932
01:03:42,750 --> 01:03:44,630
Sorry to be late.

933
01:03:45,410 --> 01:03:47,960
The original publisher went bankrupt...

934
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:51,800
The original is out of print, and the
contract just states "original writer."

935
01:03:51,800 --> 01:03:53,720
Other than the CEO of the publisher,

936
01:03:53,720 --> 01:03:56,500
no one directly interacted with the author.

937
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:58,890
I heard there's an agent. So, I'm looking for him.

938
01:03:58,890 --> 01:04:01,300
We wouldn't have wasted time
if you had collaborated from the beginning.

939
01:04:01,300 --> 01:04:04,200
Just stay out of this. Out!

940
01:04:06,440 --> 01:04:08,340
Excuse me.

941
01:04:08,340 --> 01:04:10,750
If the original author extends the copyright,

942
01:04:10,750 --> 01:04:12,640
does that solve the problem?

943
01:04:14,300 --> 01:04:20,100
It's the same person I was looking
for for PD Yu Jae Il.

944
01:04:20,100 --> 01:04:21,980
Jin Mu Yeong.

945
01:04:25,970 --> 01:04:27,330
Yes.

946
01:04:28,330 --> 01:04:30,790
The name sounds familiar.

947
01:04:30,790 --> 01:04:32,770
I am in touch-

948
01:04:33,930 --> 01:04:38,310
with the original author's agent.

949
01:04:38,310 --> 01:04:39,410
Good job.

950
01:04:39,410 --> 01:04:42,600
Although I'm sure you didn't expect this stupidity.

951
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:45,200
Je Yeon, contact them and set up a meeting.

952
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:48,210
- As soon as possible.
- Okay.

953
01:04:48,210 --> 01:04:50,140
Please draft the agreement.

954
01:04:50,140 --> 01:04:53,230
Based on the original contract,
the publisher and the production company

955
01:04:53,230 --> 01:04:55,210
monopolized the copyright
and the running guarantee.

956
01:04:55,210 --> 01:04:57,070
Did he get screwed-

957
01:04:57,970 --> 01:04:59,130
It was an unfair contract?

958
01:04:59,130 --> 01:05:02,150
I'd be so offended that I wouldn't
even consider an extension.

959
01:05:02,150 --> 01:05:04,150
Offer two to three times the
market price for copyright,

960
01:05:04,150 --> 01:05:06,210
and a separate running guarantee. Okay?

961
01:05:06,210 --> 01:05:11,000
All right, marketing team.
How are the press materials?

962
01:05:18,470 --> 01:05:20,370
Welcome.

963
01:05:22,600 --> 01:05:23,970
Hi.

964
01:05:24,710 --> 01:05:27,440
Yes, hi.

965
01:05:28,330 --> 01:05:30,770
What brings you here out of the blue?

966
01:05:30,770 --> 01:05:32,090
Take this first.

967
01:05:32,090 --> 01:05:34,310
Your shirt I ripped last time.

968
01:05:34,310 --> 01:05:36,550
I bought a sturdy one.

969
01:05:37,950 --> 01:05:41,560
- Took you long enough.
- Of course, you didn't forget.

970
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:43,460
Thank you.

971
01:05:45,450 --> 01:05:48,330
1. Work request.

972
01:05:48,330 --> 01:05:50,500
2. Personal request.

973
01:05:50,500 --> 01:05:53,810
- What do you want to hear first?
- Whatever is more urgent.

974
01:05:53,810 --> 01:05:56,900
The film "A World Made of Ash." Third sequel.

975
01:05:56,900 --> 01:06:01,000
The copyright of the original has expired,
so I need the author's extension.

976
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:02,320
And?

977
01:06:03,160 --> 01:06:05,500
I reviewed the draft of the contract,

978
01:06:05,500 --> 01:06:08,920
and it's the best-in-class offer,
in terms of money.

979
01:06:08,920 --> 01:06:12,680
It'll be tricky if we can't extend it.

980
01:06:12,680 --> 01:06:14,320
Could you send your agent?

981
01:06:14,320 --> 01:06:17,490
Geon No. He's my agent.

982
01:06:17,490 --> 01:06:19,740
I'll send you his number.

983
01:06:19,740 --> 01:06:21,280
This easily?

984
01:06:21,280 --> 01:06:24,160
You said you reviewed my contract.

985
01:06:24,160 --> 01:06:26,990
I'd imagine you made sure it's in my favor.

986
01:06:28,690 --> 01:06:32,400
I didn't know you trusted me that much.

987
01:06:32,400 --> 01:06:39,120
I've learned that trusting is easier
than being suspicious.

988
01:06:40,280 --> 01:06:42,090
What's number two?

989
01:06:42,090 --> 01:06:46,180
Your old contract was ridiculous-

990
01:06:46,180 --> 01:06:49,120
I meant, it's not great.

991
01:06:49,120 --> 01:06:50,910
If that happens again,

992
01:06:50,910 --> 01:06:55,610
air your grievance and share
how you were screwed over.

993
01:06:55,610 --> 01:06:59,320
We can curse them out together and feel better.

994
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:01,740
I'm great at cursing.

995
01:07:01,740 --> 01:07:04,330
In order to curse them out,

996
01:07:04,330 --> 01:07:08,710
I need to go back into the past and regurgitate...

997
01:07:10,000 --> 01:07:12,270
That's harder.

998
01:07:13,500 --> 01:07:15,970
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, no.

999
01:07:15,970 --> 01:07:17,590
Why would you be?

1000
01:07:18,590 --> 01:07:22,090
Oh, right. You put the snapdragon
in a vase, right?

1001
01:07:22,090 --> 01:07:24,410
- Yes.
- Do you even have a vase at home?

1002
01:07:24,410 --> 01:07:26,590
- I think so...
- "I think so"?

1003
01:07:26,590 --> 01:07:28,430
Wait a minute.

1004
01:07:46,450 --> 01:07:48,770
Hello, CEO.

1005
01:07:50,110 --> 01:07:53,700
Oh, I was able to contact the original author.

1006
01:07:53,700 --> 01:07:55,730
As you know, his agent will come in.

1007
01:07:55,730 --> 01:07:57,920
How disappointing.

1008
01:07:57,920 --> 01:08:01,200
I wanted to meet the face behind the name.

1009
01:08:03,150 --> 01:08:06,240
How come my eyes hurt so much today?

1010
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:11,110
 

1011
01:08:11,110 --> 01:08:13,880
 

1012
01:08:15,390 --> 01:08:17,680
The official article is up.

1013
01:08:17,680 --> 01:08:19,600
The sitcom was so great.

1014
01:08:19,600 --> 01:08:21,250
Weren't you a baby back then?

1015
01:08:21,250 --> 01:08:24,610
Gosh, it's all online these days.

1016
01:08:24,610 --> 01:08:28,500
Plus, I met Bebop in person.

1017
01:08:29,340 --> 01:08:32,070
Is Sunwoo Hae still good-looking?

1018
01:08:32,070 --> 01:08:34,930
He was pretty cute when he was little.

1019
01:08:34,930 --> 01:08:36,800
Did he do the show because
he needs sponsorships?

1020
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:39,230
Is it okay for Sunwoo Hae to go on TV?

1021
01:08:39,230 --> 01:08:41,430
His career ended when he scammed people.

1022
01:08:41,430 --> 01:08:45,590
Really? He didn't look like a scammer.

1023
01:08:45,590 --> 01:08:47,490
He seemed like a nice person.

1024
01:08:47,490 --> 01:08:50,130
You're so naive.

1025
01:08:50,130 --> 01:08:54,000
Look up "Sunwoo Hae scam" online.

1026
01:08:54,000 --> 01:08:56,800
No, man...

1027
01:08:56,800 --> 01:09:00,200
Right. Did that video get taken down?

1028
01:09:00,200 --> 01:09:02,950
I watched it. The kid was fierce.
Not a single tear.

1029
01:09:02,950 --> 01:09:07,280
That felt like acting, too.
Doesn't it give you chills?

1030
01:09:07,280 --> 01:09:11,030
I'm sure he knows, too.
That he caused his mom's death.

1031
01:09:14,000 --> 01:09:18,320
Let's not rehash old news.

1032
01:09:18,320 --> 01:09:20,300
It's so tacky. What are you doing?

1033
01:09:20,300 --> 01:09:21,540
What did you just say?

1034
01:09:21,540 --> 01:09:23,870
This is not cool.

1035
01:09:23,870 --> 01:09:26,060
It embarrasses me just by listening to it.

1036
01:09:26,060 --> 01:09:28,760
Why don't you fend for yourself
instead of meddling?

1037
01:09:28,760 --> 01:09:31,070
You can't even take care of your actress.

1038
01:09:31,070 --> 01:09:34,110
I let it slide because you're a woman,
and you think you can act out, huh?

1039
01:09:34,110 --> 01:09:36,600
What did you let slide?

1040
01:09:36,600 --> 01:09:38,580
I have no idea what you're talking about.

1041
01:09:38,580 --> 01:09:40,940
What did you say? You crazy...

1042
01:09:40,940 --> 01:09:43,850
Hey, hey. Je Yeon, stop.

1043
01:09:43,850 --> 01:09:48,350
Stop what? Did I trash you or your mother?

1044
01:09:48,350 --> 01:09:50,320
Why are you overacting?

1045
01:09:50,320 --> 01:09:52,180
You have no idea about other people's lives.

1046
01:09:52,180 --> 01:09:55,470
Making assumptions is just vulgar.

1047
01:09:55,470 --> 01:09:57,550
- How dare you?
- Stop, stop!

1048
01:09:57,550 --> 01:09:59,210
Stop! Stop, stop!

1049
01:09:59,210 --> 01:10:00,700
Let go.

1050
01:10:01,600 --> 01:10:03,020
Who the hell are you?

1051
01:10:03,840 --> 01:10:04,980
What is this?

1052
01:10:04,980 --> 01:10:06,460
I didn't have a sponsor.

1053
01:10:06,460 --> 01:10:09,320
People who stole my name are the scammers.

1054
01:10:09,320 --> 01:10:11,630
I worked my ass off to pay that money back.

1055
01:10:12,600 --> 01:10:17,400
And I know I caused my mom's death.

1056
01:10:20,090 --> 01:10:23,020
How dare you lay a finger on her,
you son of a bitch.

